Hello,

I know many of my bug reports are from our own patched kernel.  I have fixed at least most
of the iwlwifi related crashes, and posted some code for comment and such.  There is always
the chance that the crashes come from my patches in the first place.

I built a 6.18.16+ stable kernel, and added only the 1-4 work-queue debugging patches, and ran
some stress test to try to reproduce the regdom related deadlock.  I haven't hit that so far, but I did
hit two kernel crashes.  They looked somewhat similar, so only attaching one of them.

This is really just FYI, as previous email has already discussed some specific crashes
and work-arounds/fixes.

Thanks,
Ben

